Key Match Events: Jalen Green scored 33 points to lead the Houston Rockets to a 119-115 win over the Los Angeles Lakers.
Fred VanVleet grabbed a key steal late in the game to help secure the victory for the Rockets.
Amen Thompson added 23 points and a career-high 16 rebounds in his return after a two-game suspension.
A basket by LeBron James got the Lakers within 117-115 with eight seconds to go.
Alperen Sengun missed 1 of 2 free throws, giving the Lakers a chance to tie the game.
VanVleet stole the inbounds pass intended for James and made 1 of 2 free throws to secure the victory.
Anthony Davis had 30 points and 13 rebounds for the Lakers.
LeBron James added 21 points, 13 rebounds, and nine assists.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets had 52 points in the paint compared to 40 by the Lakers.
